      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) are directly linked to the clinical risk hypothesis and the COU decision.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the vertebral column; yield force defines the onset of permanent deformation; force at 40 mm represents the ASTM F1717 standard performance endpoint. All three QoIs are directly relevant to the clinical performance claim and the 510(k) submission decision."
